<p>What happens when you comment out <code>syncEncoders();</code>? I’m not too familiar with analog encoders but from what I’ve researched they work similar to absolute encoders in having their positions always being known, so you shouldn’t need to reset them. Instead have <code>syncEncoders()</code> sync the relative encoder and absolute encoder.</p>
<p>We do something like this, note this is for CANcoders, and will be different with analog encoders.</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">    void syncRelativeToAbsoluteEncoder() {
        if(mTurnEncoder.getVelocity() &gt;= 0.5) {
            return;
        }

        double turnEncoderPosition = mTurnEncoder.getPosition();
        double absoluteEncoderPosition = getAbsoluteAngle().getRadians();
        double diff = absoluteEncoderPosition - turnEncoderPosition;

        Logger.recordOutput("DriveModule/" + name + "/CANCoder Position", absoluteEncoderPosition);
        Logger.recordOutput("DriveModule/" + this.name + "/Turning Motor Encoder Position", turnEncoderPosition);
        Logger.recordOutput("DriveModule/" + this.name + "/Turning Motor CANCoder Difference", diff);

        if(Math.abs(diff) &gt; 0.02) {
            Logger.recordOutput("DriveModule/" + this.name + "/IsUpdatingEncoder", true);
            mTurnEncoder.setPosition(getAbsoluteAngle().getRadians());
        } else {
            Logger.recordOutput("DriveModule/" + this.name + "/IsUpdatingEncoder", false);
        }
    }
</code></pre>","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"posts_count":9,"updated_at":"2025-02-20T16:25:51.202Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":1,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":71,"readers_count":70,"score":19.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":492412,"topic_slug":"swerve-will-not-turn-modules-to-straight-on-enable","display_username":null,"primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":68816,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/swerve-will-not-turn-modules-to-straight-on-enable/492412/2","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3534304,"name":null,"username":"ohno","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/o/34f0e0/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-02-20T16:37:52.213Z","cooked":"<p>So you’re saying just replace my current SyncEncoders with a your syncRelativeToAbsoluteEncoder, modified for my absolute encoder? the original function of the SyncEncoders function was to do that.</p>","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"posts_count":9,"updated_at":"2025-02-20T17:53:46.552Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":2,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":2,"reads":45,"readers_count":44,"score":24.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":492412,"topic_slug":"swerve-will-not-turn-modules-to-straight-on-enable","display_username":null,"primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_g